35
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:24,041
I am totally not!

36
00:03:24,125 --> 00:03:25,458
I'm telling you;
they both almost died

37
00:03:25,541 --> 00:03:27,125
like right there
in the hallway!

38
00:03:31,416 --> 00:03:33,375
Um, no it's not,
like at all!

39
00:03:33,458 --> 00:03:34,958
Who's in there talking?

40
00:03:35,041 --> 00:03:37,541
She must be on a cell
phone or something.

41
00:03:37,625 --> 00:03:39,458
Come on you
always say that.

42
00:03:41,291 --> 00:03:42,166
I know that girl.

43
00:03:46,250 --> 00:03:47,791
She's in my class.

44
00:03:47,875 --> 00:03:49,375
Yozora something.

45
00:03:49,458 --> 00:03:51,291
Mikazuki, I think.

46
00:03:51,375 --> 00:03:54,208
But I've never heard her
laugh like that in class

47
00:03:54,291 --> 00:03:56,583
or, well, ever.

48
00:03:56,666 --> 00:03:58,666
She always looks
pissed as hell.

49
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:01,791
Kind of like she's
about to murder someone.

50
00:04:01,875 --> 00:04:04,375
I've never really seen
her talk to anybody.

51
00:04:04,458 --> 00:04:06,000
Crazy.

52
00:04:06,083 --> 00:04:08,041
Hold on this is
officially weird.

53
00:04:08,125 --> 00:04:09,708
She's not talking
on the phone at all!

54
00:04:13,750 --> 00:04:14,833
What the hell?

55
00:04:14,916 --> 00:04:16,750
Who's she talking to?

56
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:18,250
Is there somebody
hiding in there?

57
00:04:20,166 --> 00:04:22,000
A girl talking to
an invisible thing

58
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:23,875
in an empty classroom at dusk.

59
00:04:26,208 --> 00:04:27,750
You know, this
sounds exactly

60
00:04:27,833 --> 00:04:30,125
like the beginning of a
book I just started reading.

61
00:04:32,041 --> 00:04:33,833
Next, after
various obstacles,

62
00:04:33,916 --> 00:04:36,083
I discover her secret
and ultimately defend her

63
00:04:36,166 --> 00:04:40,166
by fighting and killing
"a thing not of this World".

64
00:04:40,250 --> 00:04:44,416
Then we would, naturally,
uh, Fall in, uh, love.

65
00:04:44,500 --> 00:04:46,333
I guess.

66
00:04:46,416 --> 00:04:49,500
You know what Tomo I think
I do remember that...

67
