Huh?

68
00:05:14,250 --> 00:05:16,000
That's what she
usually looks like.

69
00:05:17,333 --> 00:05:20,583
But she was so cute
when she was laughing.

70
00:05:20,666 --> 00:05:22,375
What do you want?

71
00:05:22,458 --> 00:05:24,958
I... I was just wondering.

72
00:05:25,041 --> 00:05:26,500
Do you, like, see
ghosts and stuff?

73
00:05:26,583 --> 00:05:27,916
What?

74
00:05:28,000 --> 00:05:30,541
Uh, no. cause
ghosts don't exist.

75
00:05:30,625 --> 00:05:32,375
Well then, who have
you been talking to?

76
00:05:32,458 --> 00:05:33,666
You were watching me?

77
00:05:42,416 --> 00:05:43,875
Look. I was having
a conversation

78
00:05:43,958 --> 00:05:45,625
with my best friend ever.

79
00:05:45,708 --> 00:05:47,208
She's made of air okay!

80
00:05:56,875 --> 00:05:58,625
You have an air friend?

81
00:05:58,708 --> 00:06:00,625
What the crap is that?

82
00:06:00,708 --> 00:06:02,666
It's exactly what
I said it was.

83
00:06:02,750 --> 00:06:04,958
You've heard of an "air
guitar" before, haven't you?

84
00:06:05,041 --> 00:06:06,666
She's like that
but cooler.

85
00:06:06,750 --> 00:06:07,916
So let's see.

86
00:06:08,000 --> 00:06:09,916
You pretend someone is
there and talk to them

87
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,208
like they're
talking back to you?

88
00:06:11,291 --> 00:06:12,791
I'm not pretending.

89
00:06:12,875 --> 00:06:14,500
Tomo exists you big jerk.

90
00:06:14,583 --> 00:06:17,000
See she's right
here next to me!

91
00:06:17,083 --> 00:06:19,583
For example Tomo and I were just
talking about this one time

92
00:06:19,666 --> 00:06:20,875
when we went
to a theme park

93
00:06:20,958 --> 00:06:22,333
back when we were
in middle school.

94
00:06:22,416 --> 00:06:24,000
This group of guys was
totally hitting on us

95
00:06:24,083 --> 00:06:24,916
while we were there.

96
00:06:25,000 --> 00:06:26,166
I mean it was ridiculous

97
00:06:26,250 --> 00:06:27,791
so I decided to
pretend one of them

98
00:06:27,875 --> 00:06:28,958
was going to be our hot
new homeroom teacher.

99
00:06:29,041 --> 00:06:30,166
You just said you
were pretending!

100
00:06:30,250 --> 00:06:32,625
Shut up! The point is
it really happened!

101
00:06:34,125 --> 00:06:35,541
Oh really?

102
00:06:35,625 --> 00:06:37,166
How much of it
really happened?

103
00:06:37,250 --> 00:06:38,791
The part where I was
in middle school.

104
00:06:38,875 --> 00:06:41,250
So only ninety--nine percent
of it was a complete lie?

105
00:06:41,333 --> 00:06:42,625
I was hoping the
amusement park

106
00:06:42,708 --> 00:06:44,250
would at least
turn out to be real.

107
00:06:44,333 --> 00:06:46,041
Seriously who
would want to go

108
00:06:46,125 --> 00:06:47,250
to an amusement
park by themself?

109
00:06:47,333 --> 00:06:48,750
You just admitted
you were alone!

110
00:06:48,833 --> 00:06:50,416
Stop! Go ahead
and get over it

111
00:06:50,500 --> 00:06:52,958
because Tomo is
unbelievably adorable.

112
00:06:53,041 --> 00:06:54,416
That chick is
off her rocker.

113
00:06:54,500 --> 00:06:55,916
This cannot end well.

114
00:06:56,000 --> 00:06:58,958
So this is really about
self-- preservation.

115
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:00,541
What is that look for?

116
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:01,791
I dunno.

117
00:07:01,875 --> 00:07:03,750
Wouldn't it be a lot
easier for you to just,

118
00:07:03,833 --> 00:07:06,250
you know, make a
real friend instead.

119
00:07:06,333 --> 00:07:08,500
Not an "air" friend
like adorable Tomo.

120
00:07:08,583 --> 00:07:11,208
But an actual
living person.

121
00:07:11,291 --> 00:07:14,041
Yeah well I would
if I could thank you.

122
00:07:14,125 --> 00:07:15,791
Shocking that you can't.

123
00:07:17,958 --> 00:07:19,708
And just who
are you to talk?

124
00:07:19,791 --> 00:07:21,541
You're that new kid
everyone's afraid of,

125
00:07:21,625 --> 00:07:22,875
isn't that right?

126
00:07:22,958 --> 00:07:25,041
I've been at this school
for well over a month now.

127
00:07:25,125 --> 00:07:26,625
I'm hardly a new kid.

128
00:07:26,708 --> 00:07:28,541
What's your name?

129
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:31,750
It's Kodaka Hasegawa.

130
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,958
It seems to me you have
no right to say anything

131
00:07:34,041 --> 00:07:35,541
about having friends Kodaka.

132
00:07:35,625 --> 00:07:37,125
First name basis already?

133
00:07:37,208 --> 00:07:38,750
So an entire
month has passed

134
00:07:38,833 --> 00:07:40,916
and you still haven't
made a single friend yet.

135
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:42,458
Wouldn't you say
that's a little pathetic?

136
00:07:42,541 --> 00:07:44,375
Hey! You only
have an air friend!

137
00:07:44,458 --> 00:07:45,875
Where the hell
do you get off?

138
00:07:45,958 --> 00:07:48,166
There's no reason
to be rude to her.

139
00:07:48,250 --> 00:07:50,458
My friend Tomo is
adorable and crazy smart.

140
00:07:50,541 --> 00:07:52,166
And she's also
an amazing athlete

141
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:53,458
and the absolute
best friend a girl

142
00:07:53,541 --> 00:07:55,416
like me could
ever hope to have!

143
00:07:55,500 --> 00:07:56,416
What's more.

144
00:07:57,958 --> 00:08:00,541
She would never even dream
about stabbing me in the back.

145
00:08:05,333 --> 00:08:07,041
It's not a mystery.

146
00:08:07,125 --> 00:08:09,250
There's nothing else I can do.

147
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,875
I don't know how
to make friends.

148
00:08:13,416 --> 00:08:16,458
Yeah, I'm not really
that great at it either.

149
00:08:16,541 --> 00:08:18,500
Did you not have any
friends at your old school?

150
00:08:18,583 --> 00:08:19,916
Of course I did.

151
00:08:20,000 --> 00:08:22,125
Don't you still
talk to them?

152
00:08:22,208 --> 00:08:24,541
He said he would text me,
but I haven't heard from him.

153
00:08:24,625 --> 00:08:26,041
Maybe you misunderstood
and just like,

154
00:08:26,125 --> 00:08:27,541
thought you were friends.

155
00:08:27,625 --> 00:08:28,833
Maybe shut up.

156
00:08:30,791 --> 00:08:31,875
Fine, then.

157
00:08:31,958 --> 00:08:33,416
You know, if you wanted,

158
00:08:33,500 --> 00:08:35,500
you could try to pay someone
to be friends with you.

159
00:08:35,583 --> 00:08:37,166
No. That's so lame, gah.

160
00:08:37,250 --> 00:08:39,208
Come on. A small
stipend every week

161
00:08:39,291 --> 00:08:41,458
for spending time
together at school.

162
00:08:41,541 --> 00:08:43,583
Like a prostitute?

163
00:08:43,666 --> 00:08:45,500
What is that, a
friend--stitute?

164
00:08:45,583 --> 00:08:48,291
No, it's a basic contract.

165
00:08:48,375 --> 00:08:50,541
Yeah. There's nothing
wrong with a contract!

166
00:08:50,625 --> 00:08:53,208
Or you could just ask
someone to be your friend.

167
00:08:54,583 --> 00:08:56,583
I've seen people do that
on after school specials,

168
00:08:56,666 --> 00:08:58,875
but I don't really get it.

169
00:08:58,958 --> 00:09:00,375
You ask someone
to be friends,

170
00:09:00,458 --> 00:09:03,791
and the moment they agree,
a friendship is suddenly formed.

171
00:09:03,875 --> 00:09:06,791
Even if you'd never spoken
to each other before then.

172
00:09:06,875 --> 00:09:09,541
What if you never even
talk after getting approval?

173
00:09:09,625 --> 00:09:11,416
Can you still consider that
person to be your friend?

174
00:09:13,416 --> 00:09:16,000
Yeah, well I guess
I can't really blame you.

175
00:09:16,083 --> 00:09:18,000
It's not my thing either.

176
00:09:18,083 --> 00:09:19,416
Besides I'm
pretty independent

177
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,541
so it's not like I need
to have any friends.

178
00:09:21,625 --> 00:09:23,583
Right.

179
00:09:23,666 --> 00:09:26,291
Not having friends must be
so hard on that poor girl.

180
00:09:26,375 --> 00:09:28,416
Condescension has to be
my least favorite thing

181
00:09:28,500 --> 00:09:29,875
in the whole world.

182
00:09:29,958 --> 00:09:30,916
Well.

183
00:09:31,000 --> 00:09:32,750
I can understand.

184
00:09:32,833 --> 00:09:34,041
For whatever reason,

185
00:09:34,125 --> 00:09:35,875
people think if you don't
have a lot of friends

186
00:09:35,958 --> 00:09:38,000
there's something
wrong with you.

187
00:09:38,083 --> 00:09:39,750
I don't think
that's true, though.

188
00:09:39,833 --> 00:09:42,041
At least I hope it's not.

189
00:09:42,125 --> 00:09:44,083
I'm perfectly
fine being alone.

190
00:09:44,166 --> 00:09:46,250
Having a few general
acquaintances at school.

191
00:09:46,333 --> 00:09:49,250
Those types of superficial
friends are enough for me.

192
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,416
Yeah, but still.

193
00:09:50,500 --> 00:09:51,791
I have to admit.

194
00:09:51,875 --> 00:09:53,625
It would be nice to
have a real friend.

195
00:10:00,208 --> 00:10:02,500
-What about school clubs?
-No way.

196
00:10:02,583 --> 00:10:04,000
Why's that a bad idea?

197
00:10:04,083 --> 00:10:06,500
Because we're in
our second year.

198
00:10:06,583 --> 00:10:08,875
Club--based friendships
have already been established.

199
00:10:10,250 --> 00:10:12,250
It'd be too embarrassing
to join one now.

200
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:14,125
Not to mention
completely obvious.

201
00:10:14,208 --> 00:10:15,333
I guess that's true.

202
00:10:16,583 --> 00:10:18,333
If you're only joining
a club to make friends

203
00:10:18,416 --> 00:10:20,208
and not because you
share an interest,

204
00:10:20,291 --> 00:10:22,208
you're only going to
screw with their dynamic.

205
00:10:22,291 --> 00:10:23,833
You'll end up being
the one loser member

206
00:10:23,916 --> 00:10:25,291
with nothing to offer.

207
00:10:25,375 --> 00:10:27,125
Why would they even
want you to join?

208
00:10:28,166 --> 00:10:29,625
She's got a point.

209
00:10:29,708 --> 00:10:31,583
I'd only join a club
to meet people;

210
00:10:31,666 --> 00:10:33,708
I don't really have
any other reason.

211
00:10:33,791 --> 00:10:35,833
And I would hate to bug them
if they were already friends.

212
00:10:35,916 --> 00:10:37,041
That would suck.

213
00:10:43,666 --> 00:10:44,958
That's perfect.

214
00:10:45,041 --> 00:10:46,000
A club!

215
00:10:52,750 --> 00:10:54,083
See you later, Kodaka!

216
00:11:15,083 --> 00:11:16,750
Why my hair looks like this?

217
00:11:16,833 --> 00:11:18,791
Oh, well, my late
mother was English,

218
00:11:18,875 --> 00:11:20,958
so I get it from her.

219
00:11:21,041 --> 00:11:22,125
I, mean. Hey.

220
00:11:22,208 --> 00:11:24,541
It's not really PC,
but have at it.

221
00:11:24,625 --> 00:11:25,625
Thank you.

222
00:11:25,708 --> 00:11:26,916
It was pretty difficult,

223
00:11:27,000 --> 00:11:28,750
but I guess time heals
all wounds, right?

224
00:11:31,375 --> 00:11:33,291
My father decided to
go abroad for work.

225
00:11:33,375 --> 00:11:35,041
I started going to Saint
Chronica's Academy

226
00:11:35,125 --> 00:11:36,583
in Tooyashi then,

227
00:11:36,666 --> 00:11:37,791
but my first day of school,

228
00:11:37,875 --> 00:11:39,041
I took the wrong bus

229
00:11:39,125 --> 00:11:40,625
and ended up getting
there really late.

230
00:11:43,125 --> 00:11:45,291
When I finally arrived
at the academy.

231
00:11:45,375 --> 00:11:47,083
I was on the verge of tears.

232
00:11:49,541 --> 00:11:51,625
Compared to crusading
armies, Saladin's army.

233
00:11:55,625 --> 00:11:57,333
Hello.

234
00:11:57,416 --> 00:11:58,541
I'm, uh.

235
00:11:58,625 --> 00:11:59,833
The transfer student.

236
00:11:59,916 --> 00:12:01,708
Okay. Great!

237
00:12:01,791 --> 00:12:03,708
My name is Kodaka.

238
00:12:03,791 --> 00:12:05,208
Nice to be here!

239
00:12:07,916 --> 00:12:09,666
Oh no, Miss Osada!

240
00:12:09,750 --> 00:12:10,791
Did he just attack her?

241
00:12:10,875 --> 00:12:12,041
Delinquent, much?

242
00:12:12,125 --> 00:12:13,125
-He's new here?

243
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:14,083
-What's up with his hair?

244
00:12:25,833 --> 00:12:27,500
I forgot my book.

245
00:12:29,750 --> 00:12:32,041
Uh. Here!
Take mine!

246
00:12:32,125 --> 00:12:33,750
Oh, thanks?

247
00:12:36,583 --> 00:12:39,208
By the evening
of my first day.

248
00:12:39,291 --> 00:12:41,541
The whole school
had heard the rumor.

249
00:12:41,625 --> 00:12:43,208
I was a thug who
stole the book

250
00:12:43,291 --> 00:12:45,083
of the poor girl
sitting next to me.

251
00:12:50,916 --> 00:12:52,375
It's been a
month since then.

252
00:12:52,458 --> 00:12:54,500
And I still haven't been
able to redeem myself

253
00:12:54,583 --> 00:12:56,833
for that first day fail.

254
00:12:56,916 --> 00:12:58,250
See you later, Kodaka!

255
00:13:01,583 --> 00:13:04,916
What a weird girl.

256
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,625
I did like that she
said my first name;

257
00:13:06,708 --> 00:13:08,041
I haven't heard
that at school, yet.

